WEBVTT

00:44.973 --> 00:46.969
(INSECTS CHIRRING)

00:58.021 --> 00:59.817
(CROWS CAWING IN DISTANCE)

01:16.334 --> 01:17.870
(HORSE NEIGHING)

01:17.905 --> 01:19.004
BOY: No!

01:19.040 --> 01:20.706
(HORSE WHEEZING)

01:24.376 --> 01:25.909
(HORSE WHIMPERS SOFTLY)

01:29.755 --> 01:31.750
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:39.832 --> 01:41.529
-(HORSE CRIES OUT)
-Oh!

01:43.536 --> 01:44.862
(PANTING)

01:56.614 --> 01:57.743
(SIGHS)

02:00.686 --> 02:01.854
(HORSE GROANS)

02:01.889 --> 02:03.378
MAN:<i> When someone</i>
<i> you love dies...</i>

02:03.414 --> 02:05.124
(HORSE NEIGHING)

02:08.058 --> 02:10.721
<i> ...you will know emptiness.</i>

02:10.756 --> 02:12.024
-(WIRE SNAPS FROM TENSION)
-(BOY SCREAMS)

02:12.060 --> 02:13.495
(CROWS CAWING)

02:14.893 --> 02:17.400
<i> You will know what it is</i>
<i> to be completely</i>

02:18.430 --> 02:19.897
<i> and utterly alone.</i>

02:24.041 --> 02:25.738
<i> You will never forget...</i>

02:26.404 --> 02:27.674
(CROWS CAWING)

02:29.948 --> 02:31.843
<i> ...and you will never...</i>

02:33.147 --> 02:35.781
<i> ever forgive.</i>

02:37.881 --> 02:40.291
(ROGUISH ELECTRONIC
MUSIC PLAYING)

03:41.952 --> 03:43.255
(TRAINS RUMBLING)

03:57.704 --> 03:59.271
(PHONE VIBRATING)

04:10.044 --> 04:11.508
(SIGHS)

04:11.543 --> 04:13.214
-Zadie?
<i> -Shelly.</i>

04:13.249 --> 04:15.116
Did you see what I sent you?

04:15.151 --> 04:17.152
SHELLY:<i> No. What is it?</i>

04:17.187 --> 04:19.285
I showed the video to someone.

04:19.320 --> 04:20.622
I think they found out.

04:21.488 --> 04:23.053
What the fuck is going on?

04:24.061 --> 04:25.462
<i> Check your texts.</i>

04:30.232 --> 04:31.967
(LAUGHTER ON VIDEO)

04:32.002 --> 04:33.096
MAN:<i> Hey, Shelly.</i>

04:35.808 --> 04:37.276
WOMAN:<i> Oh, stop!</i>

04:39.207 --> 04:40.305
(GASPS SOFTLY)

04:40.340 --> 04:41.543
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

04:41.578 --> 04:43.876
ZADIE:<i> What the fuck?</i>
<i> What did you do to her?</i>

04:47.711 --> 04:48.980
Where did you get this?

04:49.513 --> 04:50.548
Dom shot it.

04:50.583 --> 04:52.720
Look, we can get him with this.

04:53.751 --> 04:55.154
He's not invincible, Shelly.

04:55.189 --> 04:57.086
Yes, he is.

04:57.121 --> 04:59.793
I'm getting my shit
and getting the fuck out.

05:01.625 --> 05:02.832
Come with me.

05:02.867 --> 05:04.230
You and Dom.

05:04.265 --> 05:05.695
<i> The three of us.</i>

05:05.730 --> 05:07.403
Why the fuck did you do this?

05:07.438 --> 05:09.000
ZADIE: It's not safe
for us here anymore.

05:10.408 --> 05:12.177
SHELLY:<i> Stay there.</i>
<i> I'm coming to you.</i>

05:12.212 --> 05:13.706
ZADIE: I think
they've got someone on me.

05:13.742 --> 05:15.407
If they're following me,
they're following you.

05:15.442 --> 05:16.645
WOMAN 2: Hello, Zadie.

05:18.213 --> 05:19.318
SHELLY:<i> Zadie?</i>

05:22.482 --> 05:24.488
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

05:26.958 --> 05:28.021
(DOOR CLOSES)

05:28.056 --> 05:29.493
Zadie?

05:30.960 --> 05:31.957
Zadie?

05:40.566 --> 05:41.538
(LAUGHTER ON VIDEO)

05:42.567 --> 05:43.870
MAN:<i> Hey, Shelly.</i>

05:45.911 --> 05:47.641
WOMAN:<i> Oh, stop!</i>

05:47.676 --> 05:50.113
WOMAN 2: There were
other options, Zadie.

05:50.148 --> 05:51.713
I wish you'd talked to me first.

05:52.410 --> 05:53.608
(GASPS)

05:53.643 --> 05:55.486
(WHIMPERING)

05:58.484 --> 05:59.490
(ZADIE CHOKES)

06:00.627 --> 06:01.624
(GASPS)

06:15.336 --> 06:16.967
(LINE RINGING)

06:17.002 --> 06:19.238
<i> Hi, you've reached Dom.</i>
<i> Leave a message.</i>

06:19.274 --> 06:20.737
Dom, it's me.

06:20.772 --> 06:22.445
Zadie's lost her fucking mind.

06:22.480 --> 06:24.777
She just sent me
some video that you shot.

06:24.812 --> 06:27.045
Meet me at Zadie's.
I'm gonna check on her.

06:27.953 --> 06:29.179
(CUPBOARD SCRAPES)

06:31.658 --> 06:32.754
(GRUNTS)

06:37.226 --> 06:38.320
(BUTTON CLICKING)

06:41.562 --> 06:43.567
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

07:01.547 --> 07:02.784
(TRAIN RUMBLES)

07:09.755 --> 07:11.529
(FAINT ANNOUNCEMENT ON PA)

07:20.340 --> 07:22.133
OFFICER: Whoa, whoa.
What're you doing, huh?

07:31.618 --> 07:34.346
-(GRUNTS)
-Yeah, we have a 10-50,
female in her 20s.

07:34.382 --> 07:35.416
Bringing her in.

07:35.452 --> 07:36.884
-(ENGINE STARTS)
-(SIREN WHOOPS)

07:37.618 --> 07:39.722
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

08:04.748 --> 08:06.581
INMATE 1: Say something.
INMATE 2: Wake up, Eric.

08:06.616 --> 08:07.876
Are you gonna
stand up for yourself?

08:07.911 --> 08:09.013
INMATE 1: Look at me.

08:09.048 --> 08:10.345
INMATE 2:
What're you gonna do about it?

08:10.381 --> 08:12.014
You're fucking old enough
to look after yourself.

08:12.050 --> 08:13.456
INMATE 2:
Daddy's gonna come back.

08:13.491 --> 08:14.622
-INMATE 1: We're here.
-Say something.

08:14.657 --> 08:16.088
-Hello. Are you there?
-Say something!

08:16.124 --> 08:18.127
-Nothin'? You got nothin'?
-Where's your mom right now?

08:18.162 --> 08:19.524
(HORSE CRIES OUT)

08:19.560 --> 08:20.664
Say something, son!

08:23.128 --> 08:24.869
-Wake the fuck up.
-Say something, man!

08:24.905 --> 08:26.301
(ECHOING SCREAM)

08:26.336 --> 08:27.405
Say fucking something!

08:27.440 --> 08:29.772
THERAPIST:<i> I know</i>
<i> this is hard, Eric.</i>

08:29.807 --> 08:32.367
<i> But these exercises</i>
<i> are meant to get you past</i>

08:32.403 --> 08:34.678
the destructive behaviors
that brought you here.

08:36.074 --> 08:39.050
Burying it... using drugs...
(SCOFFS)

08:39.085 --> 08:41.045
That's the easy way out.

08:41.080 --> 08:44.622
It's what allows you
to hide that pain away.

08:48.293 --> 08:50.694
You, uh, going to join us?

08:53.590 --> 08:57.129
You know, Hemingway wrote,
"The world breaks everyone,

08:57.696 --> 08:59.063
<i> "and afterwards,</i>

08:59.098 --> 09:02.604
<i> "many are strong</i>
<i> at the broken places.</i>

09:02.639 --> 09:04.906
<i> "But those</i>
<i> that will not break...</i>

09:06.309 --> 09:07.370
<i> "it kills."</i>

09:16.119 --> 09:17.149
(CLINKS)

09:17.883 --> 09:19.723
(CELL DOOR BUZZES, OPENS)

09:23.061 --> 09:24.057
(DOOR SHUTS)

09:27.464 --> 09:28.959
...group therapy after that.

09:28.995 --> 09:31.664
No phones.
No talking after dark.

09:31.699 --> 09:33.572
No fraternizing with the men.

09:39.706 --> 09:41.712
(GRIM MUSIC PLAYING)

09:58.890 --> 10:01.424
(MUSIC SOARS, FADES)

10:03.703 --> 10:06.297
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

10:13.178 --> 10:14.478
MAN: Mr. Roeg.

10:14.513 --> 10:16.247
Here's the young protege
from Vienna

10:16.282 --> 10:17.572
I was telling Marion about.

10:18.914 --> 10:21.114
It's a pleasure to meet you,
Mr. Roeg.

10:22.053 --> 10:23.149
Please.

10:23.582 --> 10:24.623
Sit.

10:28.219 --> 10:29.991
Now, you know
I was born in Vienna,

10:30.923 --> 10:34.160
a cradle of immortal music.

10:34.195 --> 10:36.931
I've lived long enough to see
some of the greats play.

10:36.967 --> 10:39.132
They tell me that
you're quite dynamic yourself.

10:41.098 --> 10:43.070
-May I borrow you?
-Yes.

10:43.877 --> 10:45.036
Um...

10:45.071 --> 10:46.777
I look forward
to hearing you play.

10:52.084 --> 10:53.179
What is it?

10:53.779 --> 10:54.950
We found her.

10:56.122 --> 10:57.513
(STOOL SCRAPING)

11:01.059 --> 11:02.023
(CLANGS)

11:05.924 --> 11:07.094
(ZADIE GRUNTS SOFTLY)

11:08.497 --> 11:09.492
(GASPS SOFTLY)

11:10.400 --> 11:12.028
(BREATH TREMBLING)

11:12.063 --> 11:13.565
MR. ROEG: It's all right, Zadie.

11:13.601 --> 11:14.673
It's all right.

11:15.439 --> 11:16.807
What's done is done.

11:17.838 --> 11:19.601
We're looking for your friends.

11:21.137 --> 11:22.208
Have you seen Shelly?

11:24.148 --> 11:25.943
No.

11:25.978 --> 11:28.049
You're a good person, Zadie.

11:29.148 --> 11:30.854
You wouldn't tell me
if you knew.

11:32.091 --> 11:33.120
Would you?

11:37.454 --> 11:40.388
I've killed hundreds
of innocents like you

11:40.423 --> 11:42.228
in the centuries
that I've been here.

11:43.193 --> 11:45.231
It never gets any easier.

11:48.504 --> 11:49.565
(MR. ROEG EXHALES)

11:51.269 --> 11:54.411
I wish
the murderers and rapists,

11:54.446 --> 11:56.715
and scum of the earth would do,

11:57.544 --> 11:58.541
but...

11:59.815 --> 12:01.753
they go to hell already,
you see.

12:03.355 --> 12:05.787
Whereas people like you,

12:05.822 --> 12:08.282
those are the souls
that he wants.

12:08.317 --> 12:10.894
That's the... the deal I made.

12:12.462 --> 12:13.732
You go to hell

12:14.795 --> 12:16.064
so I don't have to.

12:17.670 --> 12:20.596
(TEARFULLY) Please...
Please let me go.

12:21.206 --> 12:22.367
You can go.

12:24.739 --> 12:27.042
(DEMONIC WHISPERING)

12:39.388 --> 12:41.291
(CLANKS)

12:41.327 --> 12:42.860
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

12:45.022 --> 12:46.292
(BLADE SCRAPES)

12:47.927 --> 12:49.933
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

12:53.205 --> 12:55.202
(GROANING)

12:58.606 --> 12:59.976
(CHOKING)

13:18.922 --> 13:19.990
(GRUNTS)

13:20.025 --> 13:21.998
(CHILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

13:26.439 --> 13:28.070
(MAN SHOUTING INSTRUCTIONS)

13:30.201 --> 13:32.068
What the fuck is going on here?

13:32.103 --> 13:34.203
Get your shit together!

13:34.238 --> 13:35.712
You know why we still out here?

13:35.747 --> 13:37.610
It's because of your bullshit!
Huh?

13:37.646 --> 13:39.147
(ALL PANTING)

13:58.962 --> 14:00.102
Hi.

14:10.111 --> 14:11.608
They don't like you in here,
do they?

14:13.418 --> 14:15.150
No, not really.

14:17.687 --> 14:19.118
They have a thing about

14:19.153 --> 14:20.455
men and women
not sitting together.

14:20.491 --> 14:21.486
SHELLY: I know.

14:22.328 --> 14:23.455
They told me.

14:27.092 --> 14:28.064
I like your tattoo.

14:28.926 --> 14:29.967
Thanks.

14:31.702 --> 14:34.433
ERIC: "Laugh now. Cry later."

14:34.468 --> 14:36.806
It's kind of how things
have been playing out for me.

14:36.841 --> 14:38.910
Well, for me,
it's more like "cry now,

14:39.641 --> 14:40.802
"cry later."

14:46.176 --> 14:47.683
Wanna hear a joke?

14:47.718 --> 14:49.682
Uh, I don't know. Is it funny?

14:49.717 --> 14:50.981
Not really.

14:51.016 --> 14:53.254
Great. Go for it.

14:54.551 --> 14:56.653
What kind of tea
is hard to drink?

14:57.693 --> 14:58.855
I don't know.

14:58.891 --> 15:00.228
Reali-ty.

15:02.128 --> 15:03.997
Yeah. Wow. Well, that's...

15:04.032 --> 15:05.662
-(CHUCKLES)
-That's something.

15:07.066 --> 15:08.705
I'll keep working on it.

15:08.741 --> 15:10.675
Hey, time
for your group session.

15:10.710 --> 15:12.673
Here he comes,
like fucking clockwork.

15:12.708 --> 15:13.703
What's your name?

15:14.346 --> 15:15.573
I'm Eric.

15:16.149 --> 15:17.174
Shelly.

15:17.209 --> 15:18.840
I'll see you around, Shelly.

15:20.551 --> 15:21.617
(PLATE CLATTERS)

15:21.652 --> 15:23.614
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

15:44.877 --> 15:47.275
THERAPIST: If you were
forced to be silent,

15:48.074 --> 15:49.541
step into the circle.

15:51.675 --> 15:54.747
If you were made
to feel that anything wrong

15:54.783 --> 15:56.053
is your fault,

15:56.720 --> 15:58.121
step into the circle.

16:00.460 --> 16:01.888
If you were abandoned,

16:01.923 --> 16:03.828
neglected, manipulated

16:03.863 --> 16:05.964
by those who were
meant to protect you,

16:06.796 --> 16:08.395
step into the circle.

16:10.394 --> 16:13.101
If you are ready to look forward

16:13.137 --> 16:15.396
to the good things
that life will bring you,

16:15.431 --> 16:17.140
step into the circle.

16:30.447 --> 16:32.188
We're pleased you found her.

16:35.389 --> 16:37.490
We're so fond of you
and your daughter.

16:57.142 --> 16:58.148
You all right?

17:00.244 --> 17:02.612
Oh, hey. Yeah.

17:02.647 --> 17:04.751
Fuck, they really
trashed the place, huh?

17:04.786 --> 17:07.124
Um... Yeah.

17:10.759 --> 17:11.788
Is this me?

17:14.796 --> 17:15.792
(CHUCKLES)

17:17.667 --> 17:18.795
All right.

17:25.974 --> 17:28.443
These songs or poems?

17:28.478 --> 17:31.346
I wouldn't call them either.
It's just shit that I write.

17:36.446 --> 17:38.083
(ERIC SIGHS NERVOUSLY)

17:38.118 --> 17:40.089
You write beautifully.

17:40.124 --> 17:42.093
Some of this would be great
set to music.

17:42.726 --> 17:44.524
Do you play music?

17:45.331 --> 17:46.427
Used to.

17:48.195 --> 17:50.359
Well, maybe we could, um...

17:50.395 --> 17:52.499
I don't know, maybe, um...

17:54.302 --> 17:56.767
Maybe we could
play together sometime.

17:58.707 --> 18:00.468
Maybe.

18:00.503 --> 18:02.344
See how we get along.

18:03.683 --> 18:05.182
What are you doing in here?

18:05.914 --> 18:07.282
I don't know.

18:07.318 --> 18:10.781
I guess everything
just finally caught up with me.

18:23.097 --> 18:25.103
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

18:38.951 --> 18:42.250
MAN: (ON PA)
<i> Patient 005, Shelly,</i>

18:42.285 --> 18:45.018
<i> please be advised</i>
<i> you have a visitor.</i>

18:45.053 --> 18:46.322
No one knows I'm here.

18:47.760 --> 18:50.227
Hey. I'll go have a look, okay?

19:00.305 --> 19:03.531
I mean, it just looks
like fucking lawyers to me.

19:03.566 --> 19:04.736
Come on, take a look.

19:10.708 --> 19:12.444
SHELLY: (WHISPERS)
What the fuck?

19:12.480 --> 19:14.381
-(BREATH TREMBLING)
-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:14.416 --> 19:16.514
-Who are they?
-They can't find me here.

19:16.549 --> 19:17.755
If they find me here,
I'm fucked.

19:17.790 --> 19:19.586
Her room is right this way.

19:20.884 --> 19:22.420
-I've got to get out of here.
-Yeah, yeah.

19:22.456 --> 19:23.656
-They can't find me here.
-Um...

19:24.796 --> 19:26.758
-Fuck!
-Come with me.

19:26.793 --> 19:30.228
Could you give me a location
update on Patient 005?

19:30.263 --> 19:32.500
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

19:36.902 --> 19:39.868
Okay, here it is. You see
those windows up there?

19:39.904 --> 19:41.141
-Yeah.
-They'll take you out
to the yard.

19:41.176 --> 19:43.142
-Okay.
-Wait, wait, wait.

19:43.178 --> 19:44.446
You gotta get the tag off.

19:46.310 --> 19:47.477
(TAG BEEPS)

19:47.512 --> 19:49.076
Can you pick up their signal?

19:49.111 --> 19:50.551
WOMAN: (ON RADIO)
<i> They're in the laundry room.</i>

19:54.286 --> 19:55.292
(SHELLY GRUNTS)

19:56.793 --> 19:58.658
(PANTING)

20:00.127 --> 20:01.796
What're you doing?

20:01.832 --> 20:03.491
Fuck this place.

20:03.526 --> 20:05.159
I'm rehabilitated.

20:05.637 --> 20:06.729
(TAG BEEPS)

20:06.764 --> 20:09.163
<i> (DISORDER</i> BY JOY DIVISION
PLAYING)

20:13.880 --> 20:15.639
<i>♪ I've been waiting for a guide</i>

20:15.675 --> 20:17.248
<i> ♪ To come</i>
<i> and take me by the hand</i>

20:19.350 --> 20:21.150
<i> ♪ Could these sensations</i>
<i> make me feel</i>

20:21.185 --> 20:23.012
<i> ♪ The pleasures</i>
<i> of a normal man?</i>

20:25.190 --> 20:26.957
<i> ♪ Lose sensations,</i>
<i> spare the insults</i>

20:26.992 --> 20:28.688
<i> ♪ Leave them for another day</i>

20:30.757 --> 20:32.995
<i> ♪ I've got the spirit</i>
<i> Lose the feeling</i>

20:33.030 --> 20:34.496
<i> ♪ Take the shock away ♪</i>

20:43.699 --> 20:44.935
Think we fucking did it.

20:45.369 --> 20:46.409
(CHUCKLES)

20:47.812 --> 20:49.203
(ERIC WHOOPING)

20:51.917 --> 20:53.542
ERIC: Hey! Hey, hey, hey, hey.

20:53.577 --> 20:55.116
Hey, slow, slow down.

20:55.151 --> 20:56.254
-Stop.
-(SONG FADES OUT)

21:00.551 --> 21:01.919
Who were those people?

21:02.827 --> 21:04.185
A former life.

21:06.224 --> 21:07.265
Right.

21:08.360 --> 21:09.531
Got one of those.

21:14.003 --> 21:15.306
I bet you do.

21:16.237 --> 21:18.232
(MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING)

21:40.459 --> 21:41.761
(ELEVATOR DOOR CLOSES)

21:44.936 --> 21:46.896
Jesus, this is crazy.

21:46.931 --> 21:50.237
It's my friend's place.
He lives in Antigua.

21:50.272 --> 21:51.837
Lets me crash here sometimes.

21:59.212 --> 22:00.241
So, um...

22:01.313 --> 22:02.485
What now?

22:06.092 --> 22:08.150
You know,
you don't have to stay.

22:09.489 --> 22:11.120
Maybe it's safer if you don't.

22:15.735 --> 22:17.159
I want to stay.

22:19.728 --> 22:20.965
Okay. Well, then,

22:22.007 --> 22:23.638
we'll hide out here for a while.

22:25.745 --> 22:26.971
And then what?

22:30.081 --> 22:31.481
We'll hide somewhere else.

22:32.918 --> 22:34.011
Just figure it out.

22:35.446 --> 22:36.618
Good plan.

22:38.021 --> 22:39.390
It is a good plan.

22:44.764 --> 22:46.161
You stink, dude.

22:46.196 --> 22:47.723
-I'm sorry.
-(CHUCKLES)

22:47.758 --> 22:49.224
Do you mind if I use the shower?

22:49.833 --> 22:51.066
Not yet.

22:51.101 --> 22:53.063
(GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING)

23:37.981 --> 23:39.010
(ERIC MOANS)

23:46.858 --> 23:48.085
(LAUGHING)

23:49.190 --> 23:50.527
Pretty good.

23:57.897 --> 23:59.803
What's the first thing
you liked about me

23:59.839 --> 24:01.032
when you saw me?

24:01.940 --> 24:03.169
What's, um...

24:03.205 --> 24:04.569
(BOTH LAUGHING)

24:04.604 --> 24:06.400
There's like an aura about you.

24:07.044 --> 24:08.479
It feels powerful.

24:10.547 --> 24:12.373
What's the first thing
you liked about me?

24:14.113 --> 24:17.081
I thought that you were
quite brilliantly broken.

24:18.350 --> 24:20.154
You are.

24:20.189 --> 24:21.558
(SHELLY CHUCKLES)

24:26.129 --> 24:27.496
What's the, um...

24:27.531 --> 24:29.258
